ass="de1">&gt;You were outside those boundaries. You could never really have a family. Too much had happened in your life.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;What you could do is focus on your education and your fighting.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Okay, you were almost completely focused on the fighting.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Some things just never changed with you.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;“I think…”You began. “That they have their own lives to get on with. And I have mine.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Yasmine frowns at this answer you notice her ears and tail drooping.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;“You keep to yourself a lot. I wonder a lot how you ended up talking to me.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;“I don’t really have an answer for you.” You said bluntly “Things just happen I guess.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Before she can answer, the timer goes off and she practically skips over to the oven.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;Meanwhile you get a text message from Toni</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;“Ayy, u coming?” </div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You quickly send out a reply</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;“No, I’m hanging out with Yasmine tonight.”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You smiled, that would blow a gasket in Toni’s head.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;No, you weren’t gonna go to his party.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;But you were not gonna let him give you shit.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;“Oh that big ass wolf?! Fuck yeah bro, have fun ;)”</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;You did not like the implications of that winky face.</div></li><li class="li1"><div class="de1">&gt;But before you could respond to him Yasmine comes out of the kitc